{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50c5c4ee-9424-4148-8b5e-e5c404010c3f","content":"No files found in the workspace — I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding:\n```xml\nxmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\nx:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**Compiled bindings give you this for free.** With `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler resolves bindings at compile time. If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Thme}`), you get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Thme\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\nTo ensure this is active:\n\n1. **Don't disable it** — compiled bindings are on by default in .NET MAUI when `x:DataType` is present.\n2. **Treat warnings as errors** (optional, recommended) in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n   ```\n3. **Avoid `x:DataType` escape hatches** — if you set `x:DataType=\"\"` on a child element, that subtree falls back to reflection (runtime) bindings and loses compile-time checking.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can be set on any element, scoping compiled bindings to that subtree.\n- `Stepper.Value` is `double`, so you may need `int` → `double` handling (a converter or change `FontSize` to `double`).\n- For `DataTemplate` items (e.g., in a `CollectionView`), set `x:DataType` on the template's root element to type-check those bindings too.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4dc6174c-3069-4ec6-ad65-11d1c197a0b1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a conceptual conversion. I'll provide them with the guidance they need to convert their XAML page to use compiled bindings.","outputTokens":808,"requestId":"9BCE:2D9C3A:6015543:6B41795:69EC0DEE"},"id":"d6f5e3aa-7322-4abc-b26d-2c0fd9756eba","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:38.915Z","parentId":"6499ab26-2fa3-4daa-b418-f46b41b72d97"}
